    <h1>Privacy Policy - Regulatory Intelligence API</h1>
    
    <div class="last-updated">
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> July 20, 2024
    </div>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>This Privacy Policy describes how the Regulatory Intelligence API ("Service") collects, uses, and protects information when you use our regulatory compliance assistant.</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>API Usage Data:</strong> We collect metadata about API requests including timestamps, request types, and response status codes.</li>
        <li><strong>Document Analysis:</strong> When you upload documents for compliance review, we process the content to provide regulatory analysis.</li>
        <li><strong>No Personal Data Storage:</strong> We do not store personal information, document content, or analysis results beyond the active session.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Provide regulatory compliance analysis and recommendations</li>
        <li>Retrieve current regulatory updates from public sources</li>
        <li>Improve service performance and reliability</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Security</h2>
    <p>We implement appropriate security measures to protect against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction of information.</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>This service integrates with OpenAI's GPT platform and retrieves regulatory information from public regulatory bodies (FINRA, SEC, CFTC).</p>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>Document analysis and API responses are not permanently stored. All processing occurs in real-time during your session.</p>

    <h2>Contact Information</h2>
    <p>For privacy-related questions about this demo service, please contact the GPT developer.</p>

    <h2>Demo Notice</h2>
    <p><em>This is a demonstration service created for educational purposes. In a production environment, this policy would be more comprehensive and tailored to specific organizational requirements.</em></p>
